        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#99)]" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d710a-99">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>—No official record of this conversation has been found. The principal subject of
                    discussion was the distribution of captured German vessels. In the course of the
                    conversation <persName>Morse</persName> communicated to <persName corresp="#p_WWG1">Weston</persName> a draft memorandum from Land to
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWL1">Clayton</persName> on this subject.<note n="2" xml:id="d710a-99fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1009">Document No. 1009</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
